0.1 Introduction

In this Rmarkdown we are going to plot panels D, G & H. In this script we will use the the scRNAseq data from sc_analysis/04-annotation/07-join_annotation.Rmd.

0.2 Libraries

library(Seurat)
library(ggpubr)
library(cowplot)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(RColorBrewer)
library(glue)
library(stringr)
library(readr)

0.3 Setting parameters

Loading necessary paths and parameters

set.seed(123)
source(here::here("misc/paths.R"))
source(here::here("utils/bin.R"))

"{fig_pt}/{plt_dir}" %>%
  glue::glue() %>%
  here::here() %>%
  dir.create(
    path = .,
    showWarnings = FALSE,
    recursive = TRUE)

  glue::glue() %>%

0.4 Load data

Load scRNAseq data

# *sc_analysis/04-annotation/07-join_annotation.Rmd
sc_obj <- "{anot_28}/{robj_dir}/harmony_se_annot.rds" %>%
  glue::glue() %>%
  here::here() %>%
  readRDS(file = .)

mask_remove <- ! sc_obj$specific_annot %in% c("Proliferating Basal Cells",
                                              "Basal Cells", "Erithrocytes")

0.5 Panels

0.5.1 Panel A

In this panel we show the UMAP with the genes of interest identifying Glial and Glial progenitors.

feats_a <- c("Slc1a3", "Scn7a", "Slc16a2", "Dio2", "Slc6a2",
           "Plp1", "Aldh1l1", "Pdgfra", "Cspg4")

panel_a <- Seurat::FeaturePlot(
  object = sc_obj[, mask_remove],
  features = c(feats_a),
  ncol = 5,
  pt.size = 0.1) &
  ggplot2::scale_color_gradient(low = "#FFFF80FF",
                              high = "#FF0000FF")

panel_a

"{fig_pt}/{plt_dir}/Extended_23-A.pdf" %>%
  glue::glue() %>%
  here::here() %>%
  cowplot::save_plot(
    filename = .,
    plot = panel_a,
    base_height = 10,
    base_width = 30)
